8
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:03,880
DALEK: <i>Who are you?</i>
你是谁

9
00:01:04,660 --> 00:01:06,340
DALEK: <i>Answer!</i>
回答

10
00:01:41,793 --> 00:01:44,585
- JAMIE: I don't know what are you being so cautious...?
- DOCTOR: Ssh!
- 不知道你这么谨慎是为了...  - 嘘!

11
00:01:44,660 --> 00:01:46,760
JAMIE: They left the door open for us, didn't they?
他们给我们留门了, 对不

12
00:01:51,092 --> 00:01:54,394
- JAMIE: It's half past the nine o'clock.
- DOCTOR: Yes, I know.
- 这才9点半呢  - 是的, 我知道

13
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:57,680
JAMIE: They made the appointment for ten. Why have we come early?
他们约的时间是10点, 我们提前来干什么?

14
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:02,720
DOCTOR: The early bird catches the worm, Jamie.
早起的鸟儿有虫吃, Jamie

15
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:05,210
DOCTOR: Now, do be quiet, there's a good chap.
现在, 别出声, 好小伙

16
00:02:05,378 --> 00:02:07,841
DOCTOR: And for heaven's sake, don't knock into anything.
还有千万别撞上任何东西

17
00:02:11,220 --> 00:02:12,630
DOCTOR: Ssh!
嘘!

18
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,100
JAMIE: Any good, this?
有什么发现吗

19
00:02:16,273 --> 00:02:18,940
DOCTOR: It's interesting.
这很有意思

20
00:02:19,420 --> 00:02:22,620
DOCTOR: In fact, Jamie, it's quite remarkable.
事实上, Jamie, 这很令人吃惊

21
00:02:22,700 --> 00:02:26,400
JAMIE: You told me outside it said "Genuine Victorian Antiques".
在外面时你说这是“维多利亚真品古董”

22
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:28,470
JAMIE: All the stuff in here is brand new!
这里所有的东西都是新的!

23
00:02:28,644 --> 00:02:32,026
- DOCTOR: You noticed that.
- JAMIE: Of course I did. The man's a rogue.
- 你注意到啦  - 那当然. 这人是个大盗

24
00:02:32,196 --> 00:02:33,671
DOCTOR: Yes, so it seems.
是的, 看来很像

25
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:36,620
- DOCTOR: Except...
- JAMIE: Except what?
- 除非...  - 除非什么?

26
00:02:37,540 --> 00:02:41,480
DOCTOR: Except that all these things are not reproductions.
除非这些都不是重新制作的

27
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:44,280
- DOCTOR: They're all genuine.  -JAMIE: That's ridiculous!\
- 它们都是真品  - 那太荒谬了

28
00:02:44,340 --> 00:02:45,590
DOCTOR: Hey, look at this.
嘿, 看看这个

29
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:49,780
DOCTOR: "To one deed box, four guineas. "
契税箱一个, 支出四基尼
(几尼金币法定? ?

30
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:55,020
DOCTOR: This is a bill from William Deering and Son. 1866.
这是一张记账单, 属于 William Deering and Son, 1866年

31
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:56,770
JAMIE: Then it's a forgery.
那么它是伪造的

32
00:02:57,230 --> 00:03:01,290
DOCTOR: If you were going to make a forgery,
wouldn't you dirty it up a bit?
如果你要伪造一个东西, 你不会来点做旧什么的?

33
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:04,970
DOCTOR: Yellow the edges, crinkle it up? This is brand-new.
把边缘搞成黄色, 把它弄皱一点? 这张是新的

34
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:07,600
- JAMIE: I've got an idea.   - DOCTOR: What?
- 我有个想法 - 什么

35
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:10,100
- JAMIE: All the stuff in here is genuine...   - DOCTOR: Yes.
- 这里所有东西都是真的...  - 嗯

36
00:03:10,140 --> 00:03:12,380
- JAMIE: .. but brand-new. - DOCTOR: Well done.
- 但都是新的 - 说得不错

37
00:03:12,440 --> 00:03:14,240
JAMIE: That is impossible, unless...
但这是不可能的, 除非...

38
00:03:14,380 --> 00:03:18,040
JAMIE: Waterfield could have invented a time machine, like the TARDIS
Waterfield 可能发明了一架时间机器, 就像TARDIS

39
00:03:18,140 --> 00:03:20,700
JAMIE: and he's bringing this stuff back from Victorian times.
然后他从维多利亚时期带回了这东西

40
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:22,560
DOCTOR: It's not very likely, is it?
这不太可能, 对吧

41
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:26,040
DOCTOR: But the only way to find out is to ask Waterfield.
不过唯一能搞明白办法, 是去问这位 Waterfield

42
00:03:36,740 --> 00:03:38,040
WATERFIELD: Kennedy!
是 Kennedy!

43
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:46,680
WATERFIELD: What happened?
什么情况?

44
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:50,820
DALEK: <i>The human discovered our communication system.</i>
这个人发现了我们的通讯系统

45
00:03:50,950 --> 00:03:54,010
- WATERFIELD: <i>And you murdered him?</i>
- DALEK: <i>He would have betrayed us.</i>
- 然后你就杀了他?   - 他很可能出卖我们

46
00:03:54,180 --> 00:03:56,020
- WATERFIELD: <i>You don't have to kill!</i>
- DALEK: <i>Silence!</i>
- 你没必要要他的命啊!  - 闭嘴!

47
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:58,340
WATERFIELD: I won't be silent! What are you dragging me into?
我才不闭嘴! 你都把我拖到什么事里面了啊?

48
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:01,200
WATERFIELD: You destroyed a human life. Don't you understand that?
你夺走了一个人的生命, 你明白吗?

49
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:04,880
- DALEK: <i>That is of no consequence.</i>
- WATERFIELD: <i>No consequence?</i>
- 这并没有什么后果 - 没有后果?

50
00:04:04,980 --> 00:04:08,900
DALEK: <i>There is only one form of life that matters.</i>
唯一重要的就只有一种生命形式

51
00:04:09,070 --> 00:04:10,700
DALEK: <i>Dalek life.</i>
Dalek 的生命

52
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:14,360
DALEK: <i>Obey your orders, Waterfield!</i>
服从命令, Waterfield!

53
00:04:18,220 --> 00:04:22,080
WATERFIELD: No, wait! What am I to do with the body?
不, 等等! 我拿这尸体怎么办?

54
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,600
WATERFIELD: I can't...
我不能...

55
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:27,840
WATERFIELD: I can't go on with this.
我不能再继续下去了

56
00:04:30,820 --> 00:04:32,730
DOCTOR: I'm sure I heard somebody shouting.
我确定我听到有人在喊叫

57
00:04:33,420 --> 00:04:36,240
- DOCTOR: We've got to get in.
- JAMIE: What about the wire?
- 我们得进去 - 用这个线试试

58
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:38,040
DOCTOR: It's too pliable.
这太软了

59
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:15,790
PERRY: Oh! What are you doing here?
噢, 你们在这里干什么?

60
00:05:15,860 --> 00:05:18,420
- DOCTOR: You made the appointment!
- PERRY: For ten o'clock.
- 你约我们来的啊   - 说的是10点

61
00:05:18,620 --> 00:05:21,640
DOCTOR: We thought we'd be early. What are you doing here?
我觉得应该早点来. 你在这里干什么?

62
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:24,660
- PERRY: I work here.
- JAMIE: Then what are you creeping about for?
- 我在这里工作啊  - 那你怎么鬼鬼祟祟的?

63
00:05:24,940 --> 00:05:29,830
DOCTOR: I think you've got some explaining to do, Mr Kenneth Perry!
我觉得有些事情你得解释一下, Kenneth Perry先生!

64
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:31,720
PERRY: My name isn't Kenneth. It's Keith.
我的名字不是 Kenneth, 而是 Keith

65
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:33,720
PERRY: Look, I don't understand this.
你看, 我没搞懂

66
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:37,620
DOCTOR: It's Keith... Do you know a man called Bob Hall?
是 Keith ? 那你认识一个叫做 Bob Hall 的人吗?

67
00:05:37,780 --> 00:05:39,970
PERRY: He's a man Mr Waterfield employs.
他是 Waterfield 先生雇佣的一个人

68
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:44,010
DOCTOR: He keeps some very rough company, including a man called Ken.
他有些不怎么样的同伙, 其中有一个叫做 Ken

69
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:45,940
PERRY: Ken? Kennedy!
Ken? 是 Kennedy 吧

70
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,520
DOCTOR: What? What do you know about Kennedy?
什么!  你都知道Kennedy 些什么?

71
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,260
PERRY: Wait a minute. This is all too quick.
等一下, 咱们别这么快

72
00:05:49,340 --> 00:05:52,880
PERRY: I'll answer your questions if you'll answer mine.
如果你先回答我的问题, 我就回答你们的

73
00:06:26,590 --> 00:06:29,660
PERRY: This old police box was for a collector of curios.
这个警察亭是给一个收藏家准备的

74
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:33,090
- DOCTOR: But it belongs to me!
- PERRY: Why is it so important to you?
- 但它是我的!  - 为什么它对你这么重要?

75
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:37,080
DOCTOR: Because... because of what's inside it,
and because it happens to be my property.
因为它里面的东西, 因为它碰巧是我的财产

76
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:38,990
- JAMIE: Where is it?  - PERRY: At the back.
- 它在哪儿?  - 就在后面

77
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:41,240
DOCTOR: Is there another way through, this door is locked.
那还有别的路过去吗? 这个门锁住了

78
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:43,740
PERRY: We might be able to get over the yard gates.
我们得先通过院门

79
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:45,540
PERRY: You see, this door has an electric lock on it.
但你看, 这门上有一个电子锁

80
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:47,900
DOCTOR: You're going to show me where this yard is.
你要给我们指一下你说的院子在哪里

81
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:51,740
PERRY: I say, if it's a police box, shouldn't we get the police?
我说, 如果说这是一个警察亭, 我们是不是应该叫警察来?

82
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:53,700
JAMIE: Doctor!
博士!

83
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,580
PERRY: That's Kennedy!
那是 Kennedy!

84
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:17,180
DOCTOR: He's dead!
他死了!

85
00:07:17,620 --> 00:07:19,940
- DOCTOR: What are you doing?  - PERRY: Getting the police.
- 你要干什么?    - 叫警察

86
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:26,600
PERRY: Don't touch anything. I'll be as quick as I can.
别碰任何东西, 我尽量快点

87
00:07:27,390 --> 00:07:29,700
- JAMIE: Should we have let him go?
- DOCTOR: He's doing the right thing.
- 我们该让他走吗?  - 他做得对

88
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:30,640
AMIE: But the Tardis!
但是 TARDIS 呢?

89
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:33,480
DOCTOR: We'll have to find it before he comes back.
我们必须在他回来之前找到它

90
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:36,660
DOCTOR: I wonder what this telephone interference is.
我很好奇这电话干扰是怎么回事

91
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,240
JAMIE: Looks as if Waterfield's cleared out.
看起来 Waterfield 早跑掉了

92
00:07:39,460 --> 00:07:41,880
DOCTOR: Why make an appointment to see us at ten?
他为什么要约我们在10点见面呢?

93
00:07:42,020 --> 00:07:44,280
JAMIE: Obviousely he didn't know
he was going to have a fight with Kennedy.
显然他并不知道他会跟Kennedy 起争执

94
00:07:44,660 --> 00:07:46,960
JAMIE: Oh, come on Doctor, let's find the Tardis and go!
得了, 博士, 我们还是找到TARDIS 离开吧

95
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:49,510
DOCTOR: Yes, the Tardis...
是的, 找TARDIS

96
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,110
DOCTOR: How did he die?
他是怎么死的

97
00:07:51,270 --> 00:07:54,220
DOCTOR: His limbs are stiff, his hands clenched..
他四肢僵硬, 双手紧握

98
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:56,930
DOCTOR: He died in horrible agony. Look at his face.
他死的时候很痛苦, 看他的脸

99
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:59,370
- DOCTOR: Hello... - JAMIE: What?
- 咦?    - 什么?

100
00:08:02,770 --> 00:08:06,030
- JAMIE: It's your picture! - DOCTOR: Yes.
- 是你的照片    - 是的

101
00:08:07,060 --> 00:08:10,860
DOCTOR: Now, he fell like that, with his arm stretched out.
看, 他的姿势好像是要去够什么东西

102
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:18,200
DOCTOR: Jamie, go out into the hall,
and measure the length of it up to the door here.
Jamie, 你到大厅去, 量一下那里到这个门的距离

103
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:33,240
- JAMIE: 14... 15.
- DOCTOR: It's only five from the door to the wall.
- 14...15   - 从门到墙这里只有5步

104
00:08:33,300 --> 00:08:35,800
DOCTOR: There must be another room behind here.
这后面肯定还有一个房间

105
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,920
JAMIE: Hey, Doctor! There's a keyhole.
嘿, 博士! 这里有个锁孔

106
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:46,740
DOCTOR: You're right. Waterfield will have the key.
你说得对, Waterfield 应该有钥匙

107
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:48,930
DOCTOR: We'd better find something to prise it open with.
我们最好找个什么东西把它撬开

108
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,220
DOCTOR: Well...
好了...

109
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:07,560
DOCTOR: Look at this.
看看这个

110
00:09:08,380 --> 00:09:11,240
DOCTOR: That's where your telephone interference is coming from.
电话干扰就是从这里来的

111
00:09:13,380 --> 00:09:15,460
DOCTOR: This is interesting.
这很有意思

112
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:19,180
- JAMIE: Hey! The other half of your picture!  - DOCTOR: Yes.
- 嘿! 你照片的另一半!    - 是啊

113
00:09:19,260 --> 00:09:20,680
DOCTOR: Don't open that!
别打开那个!

114
00:09:29,100 --> 00:09:31,840
PERRY: This way. Along here.
这边, 在这里

115
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:38,420
PERRY: Here we are.
就这里了

116
00:09:38,660 --> 00:09:44,100
PERRY: That's funny... There were a couple of other gentlemen here.
奇怪...刚才这里还有两个人呢

117
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:48,860
PERRY: They seem to have... disappeared.
他们好像是...消失了

118
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:22,720
MOLLIE: Hello, sir.
你好, 先生

119
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:25,080
MOLLIE: Are you feeling better?
你感觉好点了吗

120
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:28,400
MOLLIE: Oh, you did have a party last night, didn't you, sir!
哦, 你昨晚肯定参加聚会了, 对不

121
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:33,630
- MOLLIE: The master sent this in for you.
- DOCTOR: The master?
- 主人要我把这个送进来   - 主人?

122
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:37,370
- DOCTOR: Mr Waterfield?
- MOLLIE: No, sir. Mr Maxtible.
- Waterfield 先生吗?   - 不, 先生. 是 Maxtible 先生

123
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:42,000
MOLLIE: Mr Waterfield came back from abroad last night, sir,
with you and the young gentleman.
Waterfield 先生昨晚才回来, 先生, 跟你和那位年轻绅士一起的

124
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:46,380
- MOLLIE: Don't you remember?
- DOCTOR: Not very well, no.
- 你不记得了吗?  - 记不太清了

125
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,360
DOCTOR: Ooh!
噢!

126
00:10:49,510 --> 00:10:51,060
MOLLIE: I'd best not wake him.
我最好不要吵醒他

127
00:10:51,230 --> 00:10:54,420
- DOCTOR: What's your name?
- MOLLIE: Mollie Dawson, sir.
- 你叫什么名字   - 我叫 Mollie Dawson, 先生

128
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:57,560
DOCTOR: This stuff works remarkably quickly.
这东西见效很快啊

129
00:10:57,780 --> 00:11:01,080
- MOLLIE: Am I to pour some more?   - DOCTOR: No, thank you, Mollie,
- 要我再倒一点吗  - 不了, 谢谢你, Mollie

130
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:04,000
DOCTOR: but you can tell me what the date is.
不过你可以跟我说说今天日期是什么

131
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:05,740
MOLLIE: The date?
日期?

132
00:11:05,820 --> 00:11:08,210
DOCTOR: Yes, I am feeling very much better,
是的, 我现在感觉好多了

133
00:11:08,380 --> 00:11:13,660
DOCTOR: but I don't seem to be able to
remember the date and where I am.
但我好像想不起来日期, 也想不起来我在哪儿了

134
00:11:13,780 --> 00:11:15,960
MAXTIBLE: Mollie, that will do.
Mollie, 这样就行了

135
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:21,300
MAXTIBLE: The answers you require, sir,
might come better from me.
你想要的答案, 先生, 可能最好由我来给

136
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:25,920
MAXTIBLE: My name is Theodore Maxtible,
and I am the owner of this house.
我的名字是 Theodore Maxtible, 我是这个房子的主人

137
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:27,610
MAXTIBLE: Pray don't get up.
请不要起来

138
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:32,220
MAXTIBLE: I have the greatest sympathy for your condition
我对你的处境深表同情

139
00:11:32,540 --> 00:11:35,240
MAXTIBLE: since I was the cause of it.
因为都是因我而起的

140
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:39,400
DOCTOR: And this is Mr Edward Waterfield, I presume.
而这位, 我猜是 Edward Waterfield 先生

141
00:11:40,180 --> 00:11:42,000
DOCTOR: You don't keep appointments, do you?
你从不守约, 对吧?

142
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:45,500
- WATERFIELD: There were circumstances.   - DOCTOR: Yes, there were!
- 出了些状况  - 是啊, 有状况!

143
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:48,940
MAXTIBLE: Please, Doctor. First things first.
拜托, 博士, 先说重要的事情

144
00:11:49,660 --> 00:11:52,960
MAXTIBLE: You asked what date it was and where you were.
你刚才问你在何时何地

145
00:11:53,020 --> 00:11:54,510
DOCTOR: Yes. Well?
是的, 怎样?

146
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:57,710
MAXTIBLE: You're in my house, some miles from Canterbury.
你在我的房子里, 离坎特伯雷只有几里路
<i>（注：坎特伯雷：英国英格兰东南部的市鎮, 离伦敦有几十公里）</i>

147
00:11:58,260 --> 00:12:03,330
MAXTIBLE: The date is June 2nd 1866.
当前日期是1866年6月2号

148
00:12:04,460 --> 00:12:08,060
DOCTOR: What do you think you're up to? You steal my property,
你知道你们在做什么吗? 你们偷了我的东西

149
00:12:08,340 --> 00:12:10,600
DOCTOR: You spirit Jamie and me 100 years back in time
你们迷倒了Jamie 和我, 弄到了100年以前

150
00:12:10,640 --> 00:12:12,120
DOCTOR: and you murder a man along the way.
你们顺道还谋杀了一个人

151
00:12:12,180 --> 00:12:14,240
WATERFIELD: We had nothing to do with the death of that man.
我们跟那个人的死没有关系

152
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:16,420
- DOCTOR: I don't believe you.   - MAXTIBLE: You will believe, Doctor.
- 我不相信你  - 你会相信的, 博士

153
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:20,000
MAXTIBLE: All of us are victims of a higher power.
我们都是受害者, 有一股强大的力量

154
00:12:20,420 --> 00:12:24,120
MAXTIBLE: A power more evil and terrible
than the human brain can imagine.
一股邪恶而可怕的力量, 远超出人类所能想象

155
00:12:24,260 --> 00:12:27,640
DOCTOR: Power? Victims? What do you mean?
力量? 受害者? 你什么意思?

156
00:12:27,860 --> 00:12:31,200
- WATERFIELD: They've taken my daughter Victoria.
- DOCTOR: Who are they?
- 他们抓走了我女儿 Victoria  - 他们是谁?

157
00:12:31,280 --> 00:12:34,260
MAXTIBLE: You will not be kept in suspense very much longer, Doctor.
你很快就会知道了, 博士

158
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:40,050
MAXTIBLE: Pray come with us, and we will show you how it all began.
请跟我们来吧, 我们跟你说明一下这一切是怎么开始的

159
00:12:42,250 --> 00:12:46,230
WATERFIELD: Doctor, do whatever it is that they ask. I beg of you.
博士, 不管他们要求你做什么, 你都照做吧, 我求你了

160
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:49,040
WATERFIELD: My daughter's life is in your hands.
我女儿的性命在你的手上

161
00:12:49,940 --> 00:12:52,500
DOCTOR: I will listen. I promise.
我会仔细听, 我保证

162
00:12:57,060 --> 00:13:00,080
DOCTOR: Is er... Is that your daughter?
那个...那是你的女儿?

163
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:04,140
WATERFIELD: No, sir. That is a painting of my wife as a young girl.
不, 先生, 那画的是我的妻子, 她年轻的时候

164
00:13:04,640 --> 00:13:09,000
WATERFIELD: She is dead now, rest her soul,
but Victoria is the image of her.
她已经去世了, 愿她安息. 不过 Victoria 长得很像她

165
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:31,140
DALEK: <i>You have not eaten.</i>
你还没有吃饭

166
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:35,300
DALEK: <i>You will eat. That is an order. </i>
你得吃, 这是命令

167
00:13:36,020 --> 00:13:38,920
- DALEK: <i>Answer!</i>  - VICTORIA: Yes.
- 回答!  - 是

168
00:13:39,180 --> 00:13:43,100
DALEK: <i>You will not feed the flying pests outside.</i>
你不得喂食外面的飞鸟

169
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:44,880
DALEK: <i>Answer!</i>
回答

170
00:13:45,700 --> 00:13:46,780
VICTORIA: Yes.
是

171
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:49,780
DALEK: <i>Move to the machine.</i>
到机器那里去

172
00:13:50,460 --> 00:13:51,680
DALEK: <i>Move!</i>
去

173
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:07,240
VICTORIA: No.
不

174
00:14:11,260 --> 00:14:12,700
DALEK: <i>Move!</i>
走!

175
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:15,150
DALEK: <i>Move!</i>
走!

176
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:28,180
DALEK: <i>The weight of your body has fallen by 17 ounces.</i>
你的体重下降了17盎司

177
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:30,740
VICTORIA: What do you expect?
你还能指望怎么样?

178
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:35,580
VICTORIA: What do you expect? For pity's sake, let me go!
你还能指望怎么样?  可怜可怜我, 放我走吧!

179
00:14:35,660 --> 00:14:37,760
DALEK: <i>Speak when you are told to speak!</i>
让你说话的时候再说话

180
00:14:42,180 --> 00:14:44,140
DALEK: <i>More food will come.</i>
还有更多食物会送过来

181
00:14:44,580 --> 00:14:48,160
DALEK: <i>Eat it, or you will be fed by force!</i>
吃了它, 否则你会被强制喂食!

182
00:15:12,460 --> 00:15:16,200
MAXTIBLE: Here we are, Doctor. This is hallowed ground.
我们走吧, 博士. 这里地方比较神圣

183
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:19,660
MAXTIBLE: Here we shall not be disturbed by the servants.
在这里我们不会有仆人来打扰

184
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:23,760
DOCTOR: Yes, very impressive.
嗯, 挺不错

185
00:15:24,860 --> 00:15:26,940
DOCTOR: Now perhaps you'll explain what all this is about?
现在也许你可以解释一下都是怎么回事了?

186
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:30,020
- MAXTIBLE: Patience, my dear sir, a little longer.
- DOCTOR: Patience?!
- 稍安勿躁, 亲爱的先生  - 稍安勿躁?

187
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:33,400
DOCTOR: You don't seem to understand what's happened.
A man has been murdered!
你们好像还没搞懂发生了什么? 都有个人被杀了!

188
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:36,080
DOCTOR: You behave as if we're going on a Sunday School outing.
你还弄得好像我们要去学校组织的周日郊游似的

189
00:15:36,260 --> 00:15:40,400
MAXTIBLE: Neither Waterfield nor I were responsible for his death. Cigar?
他的死不是 Waterfield 的错, 也不是我的错. 来根烟?

190
00:15:41,280 --> 00:15:43,340
DOCTOR: Why have you brought us here?
你为什么带我们来这里?

191
00:15:43,510 --> 00:15:47,380
DOCTOR: Who are these enemies of yours,
these ones you say control you?
你们的敌人是谁?  你说在控制你们的人?

192
00:15:47,540 --> 00:15:50,860
- MAXTIBLE: Brilliant minds, Doctor.
- WATERFIELD: They are monsters!
- 高智商的头脑, 博士  - 他们都是怪物

193
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:54,140
MAXTIBLE: Oh, I admit, Waterfield, they have behaved callously.
哦, 我得承认, Waterfield, 他们做事情很冷血

194
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,580
WATERFIELD: Inhuman monsters!
没有人性的怪物!

195
00:15:55,660 --> 00:15:57,710
- DOCTOR: Inhuman?
- WATERFIELD: Creations of the devil!
- 没有人性?   - 是邪恶的缔造者!

196
00:15:57,960 --> 00:16:00,400
- MAXTIBLE: Let me explain.
- DOCTOR: Please do!
- 我来解释一下    - 赶紧的

197
00:16:02,470 --> 00:16:07,690
MAXTIBLE: I've always been fascinated
by the concept of travelling through time.
我一直都对时间旅行这个事情很着迷

198
00:16:09,690 --> 00:16:13,910
MAXTIBLE: Waterfield here is an expert in certain technical matters,
这位 Waterfield 先生在技术方面是一位专家

199
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:17,190
MAXTIBLE: and I have the money to indulge my whims.
我也有点钱可以砸在自己的古怪想法上

200
00:16:17,350 --> 00:16:22,210
MAXTIBLE: Everything you see about you was constructed by us two.
你在这里看到的所有东西都是我们俩建造的

201
00:16:22,380 --> 00:16:26,600
- DOCTOR: To try to find a way of exploring time?
- MAXTIBLE: Yes.
- 为了找到穿越时间的方法?   - 是的

202
00:16:26,770 --> 00:16:28,440
MAXTIBLE: Now, this is my theory.
好了, 现在说说我的理论

203
00:16:29,060 --> 00:16:32,380
- MAXTIBLE: A mirror reflects an image, does it not?
- DOCTOR: Yes.
- 一面镜子可以反射图像, 对不?   - 可以

204
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:37,640
MAXTIBLE: So, you may be standing there
and yet appear to be standing 50 feet away.
所以, 你可以站在这里, 但又好像出现在50英尺之外

205
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:45,410
MAXTIBLE: Following the new investigations 12 years ago
by J Clark Maxwell into electromagnetism,
基于麦克斯韦在12年前在电磁场方面的研究

206
00:16:46,120 --> 00:16:51,120
MAXTIBLE: and the experiments by Faraday into static electricity...
以及法拉第的静电实验...

207
00:16:51,340 --> 00:16:53,220
- DOCTOR: Static?   - MAXTIBLE: Correct.
- 静电?     - 正确

208
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:58,200
MAXTIBLE: .. Waterfield and I first attempted
to define the image in the mirror,
...Waterfield 和我试验了在镜子中固定图像

209
00:16:58,340 --> 00:17:00,180
MAXTIBLE: and then to project it.
然后再投射出去

210
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:08,390
MAXTIBLE: In here, Doctor, are 144 separate mirrors.
这里, 博士, 有144面镜子

211
00:17:08,550 --> 00:17:13,460
WATERFIELD: Each is of polished metal. Each is subjected
to electric charges, all positive.
每一面都是金属抛光制成的, 还会充上电, 全都是正电

212
00:17:13,620 --> 00:17:16,160
MAXTIBLE: Like repels like in electricity, Doctor,
正如电负荷会同性相斥, 博士

213
00:17:16,260 --> 00:17:21,680
MAXTIBLE: and so we attempted to repel the image
in the mirrors wherever we directed.
于是我们尝试了在镜子间反射图像, 以让它到达我们期望的地方

214
00:17:21,960 --> 00:17:25,260
- DOCTOR: You mentioned static electricity...
- WATERFIELD: That was our last experiment.
- 你刚才提到了静电...   - 那是我们最后一个实验

215
00:17:25,780 --> 00:17:29,560
WATERFIELD: Negative and positive electricity
had failed, so we tried static.
负电与正电都失败了, 所以我们尝试了静电

216
00:17:29,860 --> 00:17:33,810
- WATERFIELD: If only we had know the powers we'd unleash.
- DOCTOR: Powers?
- 可惜我们没能早点知道, 我们会释放出什么样的力量   - 力量?

217
00:17:33,980 --> 00:17:39,040
WATERFIELD: In the middle of our final test with static,
creatures burst out of the cabinet,
在我们最后一次静电实验中, 有种怪物从柜子里面蹦出来了

218
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:43,110
WATERFIELD: invaded the house and took away my daughter.
入侵了我们的房子, 掳走了我的女儿

219
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:47,280
MAXTIBLE: Oh, my dear fellow! My dear, dear fellow!
哦, 我亲爱的朋友, 可怜的家伙 !

220
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:50,940
MAXTIBLE: We shall win through, now that the Doctor is here.
既然博士现在来了, 我们应该能赢了

221
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:52,800
DOCTOR: These creatures...
这些怪物...

222
00:17:52,860 --> 00:17:55,260
WATERFIELD: We had opened the way for them with our experiments.
是我们的实验给他们打开了大门

223
00:17:55,540 --> 00:17:58,700
WATERFIELD: They forced me into the horror of time travel.
他们强迫我进行时间旅行

224
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:01,420
WATERFIELD: They ordered me to steal a box belonging to you
他们命令我去偷你的那个亭子

225
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:05,160
WATERFIELD: and thus lure you into a trap and transport you here,
以钓你上钩, 再把你们传输过来

226
00:18:05,340 --> 00:18:07,360
WATERFIELD: ...to get you with your colleague Mr McCrimmon.
以抓住你和你的朋友 McCrimmon 先生

227
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:10,700
- DOCTOR: They knew about me?   - MAXTIBLE: They gave us likenesses.
- 他们认识我?     - 他们给了我们详细描述

228
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:13,960
WATERFIELD: What could I do? They said my daughter would die.
我能怎么办?  他们说否则我的女儿就得死

229
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:18,580
- DOCTOR: What are they called, these creatures?
- DALEK: <i>Doctor!</i>
- 他们叫什么名字, 这些怪物?   - 博士!

230
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:23,460
DALEK: <i>Now do you understand?</i>
现在你明白了吧?

231
00:18:25,560 --> 00:18:27,500
DOCTOR: Oh, yes. Perfectly.
哦, 是的, 完全明白

232
00:18:28,380 --> 00:18:29,900
DOCTOR: <i>Move back!</i>
退后!

233
00:18:31,420 --> 00:18:33,410
DOCTOR: <i>Our plan has worked.</i>
我们的计划成功了

234
00:18:33,580 --> 00:18:38,320
- DALEK: <i>We shall triumph! You will obey!</i>
- DOCTOR: Obey? What do you want?
- 我们会胜利! 你将服从!   - 服从? 你想要怎样?

235
00:18:38,490 --> 00:18:41,620
DALEK: <i>We have your time ship. We will destroy it</i>
我们得到了你的时间飞船, 我们将销毁它

236
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:43,900
DALEK: ...unless you help the Daleks with an experiment.
...除非你帮 Dalek 完成一项实验

237
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:45,040
DOCTOR: What experiment?
什么实验?

238
00:18:45,140 --> 00:18:49,060
DALEK: <i>You will help us test another human being.</i>
你得帮我们测试另外一个人类

239
00:18:49,140 --> 00:18:50,860
- DOCTOR: What sort of test?   - DALEK: <i>No questions!</i>
- 什么样的测试?   - 不许问

240
00:18:50,980 --> 00:18:53,360
- DOCTOR: I won't be your slave!   - MAXTIBLE: Doctor, I beg you...
- 我可不会做你的奴隶!   - 博士, 我求你了...

241
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:56,960
DALEK: <i>No harm will come to you if you agree.</i>
如果你同意的话, 就不会受到伤害

242
00:18:57,260 --> 00:18:59,300
DALEK: <i>Where is your companion?</i>
你的同伴在那里?

243
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:03,220
- DOCTOR: Jamie?   - WATERFIELD: He is in the house.
- Jamie?   - 他在房子里

244
00:19:03,420 --> 00:19:05,480
WATERFIELD: I have done everything you asked me to.
你们让我干的事情, 我全都干了

245
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:08,400
DOCTOR: Why do you ask about Jamie?
你为什么问起 Jamie?

246
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:12,300
DALEK: <i>He is the human being who is to be tested.</i>
他就是我们要实验的对象

247
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:15,260
- DOCTOR: What do you mean? Tested how?   - DALEK: <i>Silence!</i>
- 你什么意思? 怎么实验?   - 闭嘴!

248
00:19:15,660 --> 00:19:18,400
DALEK: <i>You will reveal nothing to your companion.</i>
你不得向你的同伴透露任何情况

249
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:22,460
DALEK: <i>Obey the Daleks! You are in our power!</i>
服从 Daleks 的命令! 你在我们的手上!

250
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:30,080
DOCTOR: What have you done with your infernal meddling?
你们到底插手干了些什么邪恶勾当?

251
00:19:34,560 --> 00:19:36,940
DOCTOR: What is this test?
实验内容是什么?

252
00:19:38,220 --> 00:19:40,440
- DOCTOR: Do either of you know?
- WATERFIELD: No.
- 你们俩谁知道吗?    - 不知道

253
00:19:40,980 --> 00:19:42,760
MAXTIBLE: I believe I do.
我想我知道

254
00:19:43,540 --> 00:19:48,680
MAXTIBLE: They, I mean the Daleks, tell me
they've always been defeated by human beings.
他们, 我是说 Daleks, 跟我说他们一直被人类打败

255
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:49,720
DOCTOR: In the long run, yes.
从长远来看, 是的

256
00:19:49,780 --> 00:19:53,900
MAXTIBLE: Possibly because of some factor possessed by humans
可能是因为人类所具有的某些特质导致的

257
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:55,760
- MAXTIBLE: that is absent in Daleks?
- DOCTOR: Possibly.
- 而 Daleks 缺这些特质  - 有可能

258
00:19:55,840 --> 00:20:00,520
MAXTIBLE: Perhaps they want to find out what it is,
and transplant it into their race?
也许他们想搞明白到底是什么东西, 然后嫁接到他们这个种族上

259
00:20:00,580 --> 00:20:05,380
WATERFIELD: But if they do do that, they ally this with
their own alien intelligence, they'll be invincible!
他们要是这样做了, 跟他们的外星智能联合起来, 他们就所向无敌了!

260
00:20:05,660 --> 00:20:07,000
WATERFIELD: Maxtible, you should have...
Maxtible, 你早就应该...

261
00:20:07,060 --> 00:20:11,430
MAXTIBLE: My dear fellow, I am merely surmising.
I know nothing definite.
亲爱的朋友, 我也只是猜测. 我也不是太确定

262
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:15,900
MAXTIBLE: Besides, what could we have done,
even if I had known for certain?
再说了, 就算我确实知道, 我又能做什么呢?

263
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:20,880
MAXTIBLE: The fact was, nay, is, they hold your daughter Victoria.
事实是, 他们关押了你的女儿 Victoria

264
00:20:21,340 --> 00:20:22,820
DOCTOR: And now they've got Jamie.
现在他们又抓了 Jamie

265
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:28,930
MOLLIE: I'm sorry, sir. I didn't mean to wake you.
对不起, 先生, 我不是故意吵醒你的

266
00:20:31,740 --> 00:20:33,240
JAMIE: It's not funny.
这不好笑

267
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:36,990
MOLLIE: The master left this for you to drink, sir.
主人把这个留给你喝的, 先生

268
00:20:37,260 --> 00:20:39,560
MOLLIE: This'll clear away the cobwebs.
他可以让你清醒一点

269
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:40,820
MOLLIE: Here you are, sir.
给你, 先生

270
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:42,520
JAMIE: Where's the Doctor?
博士在哪儿?

271
00:20:42,620 --> 00:20:45,600
- MOLLIE: He's with the master and Mr Waterfield.
- JAMIE: Waterfield?
- 他正跟主人和 Waterfield 先生在一起  - Waterfield?

272
00:20:47,300 --> 00:20:50,500
- RUTH: What are you doing here?
- MOLLIE: Just seeing to the young gentleman, miss.
- 你在这里干什么?   - 刚过来看一下这位年轻的男士, 小姐

273
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:52,110
RUTH: Go and bring some tea.
去, 端点茶来

274
00:20:52,280 --> 00:20:54,710
RUTH: Well, go along.
诶, 快去啊

275
00:20:58,120 --> 00:21:01,250
- RUTH: Please, Mr McCrimmon.
- JAMIE: You know my name?
- 请坐, McCrimmon 先生  - 你知道我的名字?

276
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:06,620
RUTH: My father told me that you and your friend
arrived last night, with Mr Waterfield.
我父亲告诉我说您和您的朋友昨晚到了, 跟 Waterfield 先生一起

277
00:21:06,780 --> 00:21:11,050
JAMIE: Your father? I'm sorry I seem to have
great difficulty in remembering anything.
您父亲?  很抱歉, 我好像什么事情都很难想起来

278
00:21:11,210 --> 00:21:14,920
RUTH: He owns this house. I'm his daughter, Ruth Maxtible.
这栋房子是他的. 我是他的女儿, Ruth Maxtible

279
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:18,460
JAMIE: How do you do? Have you seen the Doctor this morning?
很高兴认识你. 你今天早上见到博士了吗?

280
00:21:18,620 --> 00:21:21,210
RUTH: He's talking with my father. He'll be along presently.
他跟我父亲在一起谈话, 很快就会过来

281
00:21:21,370 --> 00:21:22,260
RUTH: Do you have everything you need?
您还有什么需要吗?

282
00:21:22,260 --> 00:21:25,670
JAMIE: I don't know what this stuff is, but it seems to work all right.
不知道这个东西是什么, 但它好像很有用

283
00:21:25,840 --> 00:21:28,630
- RUTH: Mollie shall bring you some tea.
- JAMIE: I'm obliged to you.
- Mollie 会给你端点茶过来的  - 我很感激

284
00:21:28,790 --> 00:21:30,740
- JAMIE: Oh, Miss Maxtible.
- RUTH: Yes?
- Maxtible 小姐  - 什么?

285
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:32,820
JAMIE: Could you tell me who that is in the portrait?
你能告诉我这张画里面是谁吗?

286
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:35,920
RUTH: That's a portrait of Mr Waterfield's late wife.
那画的是 Waterfield 已过世的妻子

287
00:21:36,340 --> 00:21:40,840
- JAMIE: She is very lovely.
- RUTH: Yes, and his daughter looks just like her.
- 她很漂亮  - 是的, 她女儿跟她一模一样

288
00:21:41,840 --> 00:21:44,380
- RUTH: You're quite comfortable?
- JAMIE: Yes, thank you.
- 请自便   - 好的, 谢谢你

289
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:06,040
JAMIE: 1866.

290
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,980
JAMIE: So that's what Waterfield's done.
原来这就是 Waterfield 干的好事

291
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:50,540
MOLLIE: Here we are, sir. I've been as quick as I could.
来了, 先生. 我尽可能快了

292
00:22:51,180 --> 00:22:52,980
MOLLIE: Shall I pour for you?
要我给你倒吗?

293
00:23:00,940 --> 00:23:05,280
MOLLIE: Poor young gentleman.
They shouldn't have given you so much to drink.
可怜的年轻人, 他们不应该让你喝那么多酒的

294
00:23:08,460 --> 00:23:12,340
- WATERFIELD: Doctor... I do ask you to consider.
- DOCTOR: I have made up my mind.
- 博士... 我真的请求你再考虑一下  - 我已经决定了

295
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:15,640
WATERFIELD: But they ordered you not to tell your friend anything.
但他们命令你不要告诉你朋友任何事

296
00:23:15,910 --> 00:23:20,040
DOCTOR: Do you think I will allow Jamie
to run into danger? No, I will not.
你觉得我会让 Jamie 陷入危险吗? 不, 我不会的

297
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:23,120
- WATERFIELD: Suppose he refuses to do what they want?
- DOCTOR: We shall see.
- 假设他拒绝干呢?   - 看情况吧

298
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:27,100
DOCTOR: He's still asleep.
他还在睡

299
00:23:27,940 --> 00:23:30,710
DOCTOR: The gas in that box of yours was pretty potent.
你那盒子里面的气体效果很强啊

300
00:23:30,760 --> 00:23:32,260
WATERFIELD: It was Maxtible's invention.
那是 Maxtible 的发明

301
00:23:37,980 --> 00:23:40,860
- DOCTOR: Jamie...
- WATERFIELD: Mollie!

302
00:23:42,500 --> 00:23:46,000
DALEK: <i>Order the Doctor to begin the test.</i>
命令博士开始实验

303
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:49,220
MAXTIBLE: But I must first explain to him what he has to do.
但我必须得先跟他解释清楚要他干什么

304
00:23:49,390 --> 00:23:51,920
DALEK: <i>Go now. Obey the Daleks!</i>
现在就去, 服从 Daleks 的命令

305
00:23:52,140 --> 00:23:57,250
WATERFIELD: But your friend is vital to the plan of these Daleks.
Absolutely essential.
但你的朋友对于这些个 Daleks 的计划很关键, 绝对重要

306
00:23:57,360 --> 00:24:00,240
DOCTOR: So it seems. So who could have kidnapped him?
看来是. 可能是谁绑架了他?

307
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:03,480
WATERFIELD: Oh, why won't you understand?
The threats they make are not idle ones.
哦, 你怎么就不明白, 他们的警告可不只是说说而已的

308
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,040
WATERFIELD: Kennedy was murdered.
Kennedy 就被杀死了

309
00:24:05,260 --> 00:24:08,060
WATERFIELD: Without your friend, our only hope is gone...
没有你的朋友, 我们唯一的期望就没有了

310
00:24:09,220 --> 00:24:12,720
WATERFIELD: unless... unless you know something.
除非... 除非你知道些什么

311
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:16,240
WATERFIELD: You seem to be well acquainted with the creatures.
你似乎对这些怪物很熟悉

312
00:24:16,410 --> 00:24:19,150
DOCTOR: Everything you say, Waterfield, is true.
Waterfield, 所有你刚才说的, 都是真的

313
00:24:19,900 --> 00:24:21,840
DOCTOR: If we cannot find Jamie
如果我们找不到 Jamie

314
00:24:22,020 --> 00:24:25,420
DOCTOR: the Daleks will take pleasure in killing everyone in sight,
这些 Daleks 会很乐意杀死所见到的每一个人

315
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:28,860
DOCTOR: and their greatest pleasure will be in killing me.
而让他们最高兴的事情, 是杀死我

316
00:24:29,480 --> 00:24:33,740
DALEK 1: <i>The humans have been told to begin the test.</i>
已经通知人类开始实验

317
00:24:34,140 --> 00:24:37,240
DALEK 2: <i>Any delay will result in death.</i>
有任何拖延都将处死

318
00:24:37,340 --> 00:24:39,130
DALEK 2:<i>There will be no delay!</i>
不允许有拖延!
